A 19-year-old artisan, Adeyinka Ademola, on Monday appeared before a  Grade 1 Area Court in Mpape, Abuja, for allegedly stealing  provisions and an HP printing machine. The police charged Ademola, who lives in Mpape, Abuja, with house breaking and theft. The Prosecutor, M.M. Austin, told the court that the defendant on Oct. 25, broke into the house of the complainant, Mr Victor Odewole, and also stole a black bag containing men sandals. He said the offence contravened  the provisions of sections 346 and 288 of the Penal Code. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. The Judge, Mr Salihu Ibrahim, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N500,000, with one reasonable surety in like sum. Ibrahim ordered that the surety must live within the court’s jurisdiction. He adjourned the case until Nov. 11, for hearing. (NAN) Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.